New Records: David Miller scored an unbeaten 59 runs from 51 balls, the highest score at the Nassau County Ground
South Africa successfully chased down a target of 103 runs to win the match
Key Match Events: South Africa's top order struggled initially, with early dismissals of Quinton de Kock and Aiden Markram
Tristan Stubbs and David Miller formed a crucial 65-run partnership to turn the innings around
Dutch bowlers Marco Jansen and Anrich Nortje put up strong performances but couldn't prevent the South African win
The match was decided in the final over with South Africa scoring 27 runs from 22 balls
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was one of several World Cup games hosted by New York in a short period, with cricket becoming familiar to the local audience
